--- STEP 1: Compute D_n(q) as a polynomial in q for small n
  D_1(q) = 1q^0
  D_2(q) = 1q^1
  D_3(q) = 2q^1 + 1q^2
  D_4(q) = 2q^0 + 5q^1 + 3q^2 + 1q^3
  D_5(q) = 14q^0 + 20q^1 + 14q^2 + 4q^3 + 1q^4
  D_6(q) = 90q^0 + 115q^1 + 72q^2 + 26q^3 + 5q^4 + 1q^5
  D_7(q) = 646q^0 + 790q^1 + 467q^2 + 168q^3 + 41q^4 + 6q^5 + 1q^6

